# Test data — pinned by SHA-256, must not be line-ending-converted.
# The pinned hashes in `tests/abng/baseline_wisconsin_bc.rs` (and
# any future tests/data/* pins) attest to the exact byte stream
# served by the upstream source. Git's autocrlf machinery would
# silently change those bytes on Windows checkouts; marking these
# paths as `binary` disables both CRLF↔LF conversion and any
# textual diff that would otherwise be useless on a 569-row CSV.
tests/data/* binary

# bench_results/ artifacts are deterministic, byte-stable outputs
# of `cargo test --ignored ...` producers. Force LF so the
# committed bytes match what producers emit on every platform.
# Without this, a Windows checkout sees CRLF in working tree,
# the byte-stability test's "render → write → readback" check
# would fail at readback, and `git diff` would be noisy across
# platforms.
bench_results/**/*.md text eol=lf
bench_results/**/*.csv text eol=lf
bench_results/**/*.txt text eol=lf
bench_results/**/*.svg text eol=lf
